# Athan Display — PWA Prayer Times & Athan Player

## Project Overview
A Progressive Web App that turns an LG V50 ThinQ into a dedicated Islamic prayer times display and athan player. The phone stays plugged in and mounted in the living room, running fullscreen 24/7.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework:** React 18 + Vite
- **Styling:** Tailwind CSS (utility-first, no separate CSS files)
- **Prayer Times:** Aladhan API (free, no API key) — https://api.aladhan.com/v1
- **Audio:** HTML5 Audio API for athan playback
- **State:** React Context + localStorage for settings persistence
- **PWA:** manifest.json + service worker for offline support
- **Deployment:** Vercel (static hosting, auto-deploy from GitHub)

## Design Requirements
- **Target device:** LG V50 ThinQ (1080x2340px, 6.4" OLED)
- **Viewing distance:** 3-5 meters across a living room
- **Always-on:** Screen stays on 24/7 while charging
- **Dark theme:** Dark green/black background (#0B1D0F base) to reduce OLED burn-in
- **Large text:** Clock should be massive (8-10rem), prayer times readable from across room
- **Minimal interaction:** Parents should never need to touch the phone after setup
- **Islamic aesthetic:** Subtle geometric patterns or gradients, green/gold accent colors

## Color Palette
- Background: #0B1D0F (very dark green)
- Primary text: #E8F5E9 (light green-white)
- Accent: #2D6A4F (medium green)
- Highlight (next prayer): #FFD700 (gold)
- Secondary text: #81C784 (muted green)
- Card/surface: #1B4332 (dark green)

## API Integration — Aladhan
- **Endpoint:** GET https://api.aladhan.com/v1/timings/{DD-MM-YYYY}?latitude=43.8384&longitude=-79.0868&method=2
- **Default location:** Pickering, ON, Canada (lat: 43.8384, lng: -79.0868)
- **Default method:** 2 (ISNA — Islamic Society of North America)
- **Available methods:** 1=Karachi, 2=ISNA, 3=MWL, 4=Umm Al-Qura, 5=Egyptian
- **Response includes:** Fajr, Sunrise, Dhuhr, Asr, Maghrib, Isha times + Hijri date
- **Caching:** Fetch once per day at midnight or on app launch, store in localStorage
- **Pre-fetch:** Get next day's times at 11:00 PM
- **Fallback:** Use cached data if API fails

## Prayers to Display
1. Fajr (dawn prayer)
2. Sunrise (not a prayer, but important reference time)
3. Dhuhr (noon prayer)
4. Asr (afternoon prayer)
5. Maghrib (sunset prayer)
6. Isha (night prayer)

## Athan Audio System
- Store MP3 files in public/audio/ (fajr.mp3, regular.mp3)
- Fajr gets a distinct athan sound from the other 4 prayers
- Sunrise does NOT get an athan
- Check time match every 15 seconds via setInterval
- Track which prayers have been called today to prevent duplicate playback
- Reset the "played" flags at midnight
- IMPORTANT: Browser autoplay policy requires user interaction first. Show a one-time "Tap to Enable Athan" overlay on first visit. Once tapped, audio is unlocked for the session.

## Settings (persisted in localStorage)
- Calculation method (dropdown: ISNA default, MWL, Egyptian, Umm Al-Qura, Karachi)
- Location (city display + manual latitude/longitude fields)
- Athan enabled/disabled per prayer
- Volume slider
- Athan sound selection (if multiple files available)
- Theme toggle (dark/light — dark is default)

