├── .cursorrules                # This file
├── vite.config.js
├── tailwind.config.js
└── package.json
```

## Code Conventions
- Functional components only (no class components)
- Use hooks for all state and side effects
- Tailwind for all styling — no separate CSS files per component
- Single-file components (no splitting into .jsx + .css)
- Use async/await for API calls (no .then chains)
- Destructure props and state
- Use semantic HTML where possible
- Comments for non-obvious logic (especially time calculations and athan scheduling)

## Screen Layout (Main Display)
```
┌─────────────────────────────────┐
│  Mon, Apr 1, 2026   7 Shawwal   │  ← Date bar
│                                  │
│                                  │
│           10:42               │  ← Large clock (massive font)
│                                  │
│      Dhuhr in 1h 23m            │  ← Next prayer countdown
│                                  │
│ ┌─────┬─────┬─────┬─────┬─────┐ │
│ │Fajr │Dhuhr│ Asr │Magh │Isha │ │  ← Prayer times row
│ │5:42 │12:05│3:31 │7:12 │8:32 │ │     (next one highlighted gold)
│ └─────┴─────┴─────┴─────┴─────┘ │
│                            ⚙    │  ← Settings gear (subtle)
└─────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Critical Reminders
- The phone is in PORTRAIT orientation
- Dark theme by default to prevent OLED burn-in
- All times are in 12-hour format with AM/PM (North American convention)
- The app must work offline after first load (service worker caches everything)
- Test on Chrome Android — that's the browser the LG V50 will use
- Settings gear should be very subtle — parents won't need it day-to-day
- Prevent screen from requesting sleep via Wake Lock API if available
